Earthquake-stricken Ecuador isnegotiating with Nigeria to have the African country lend it10,000 barrels per day (bpd) of crude for export, Deputy EnergyMinister Fernando Santos Alvite told Reuters.    He said Ecuador was negotiating a shipments schedule andthe terms of repaying the loan. Ecuador has suspended crudeexports for about five months until it repairs a pipelineruputured by a March five tremor.    Santos Alvite added Ecuador is finalizing details for aprogram under which Venezuela would temporarily lend thecountry 50,000 bpd for export. Reuter&#3;